reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I have had bad luck with tripods - or maybe you get what you pay for - because I have purchased and given up on four other tripods before finding this one. And I’m glad I did.It’s stable, solid, fully adjustable, and holds its position. It holds my iPhone with the case with no issues. I don’t feel like I need to be careful with it because parts might snap.At this point I think I’m taking it for granted, but that’s the nice thing about stuff I buy - I’m hoping for it to just work well and be able to count on it, not be fussing with it all the time. Took me a couple fails but I’m so glad I got this one. I’ve used it at least every other day since I bought it many months ago.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love it! Go to Stand!
reviews.reviewText: It's great! Sturdy and does a great job! Definitely improved the quality of my videos. I've always been hesitant about phone stands with flexible arms, but this one is really good quality. It's lightweight but heavy enough to balance and not tip over. I don't really like the spring-loaded phone holder because I tend to break my nails opening them, but it's good quality and my phone doesn't move.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy, stable and flexible.
reviews.reviewText: After selling all of my higher end camera gear (Nikon D800, lenses, etc.), I needed a good, but lightweight stand for doing product shots with my iPhone. I read a lot of reviews on various stands with flexible goosenecks, this one stood above the rest.There are *always* negative reviews of anything, so you have to discount some of them. Or at least pay attention to which product has the least number of negative reviews.A big feature for me with this stand is it comes with a Bluetooth remote to trigger a shot. Any good photographer knows if you want truly sharp pictures, you want your camera to be perfectly still. The remote allows me to keep my fingers off the camera so it shoots while being absolutely motionless.The grip for the phone is a bit tight. But that's a good thing as you don't have to worry about your phone falling out it, no matter what orientation it's at.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Holds Erchonia red/violet laser
reviews.reviewText: We bought it for the hand held Erchonia laser. It works great. The hand held laser is heavier than the iPhone but aside side from having to check it doesn’t over-balance the tripod, it works great!

reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I highly recommend this tripod. It is such a value for the money. There was basically no assembly required. And it’s so versatile. I can use it anywhere. And the full extension helps when I’m filming in different places. It is sturdy and holds my phone well without Tipping over.

reviews.reviewTitle: Gooseneck broke, emailed and they replaced !!
reviews.reviewText: The gooseneck broke and couldn't hold my s23 ultra with light (fairly heavy) I emailed and they sent me a replacement. Good customer service!
Tall, short, high, low... it does it all. The phone clamps are a bit tight, but it holds my phone safely.
